stm32l1xx.h File Reference

CMSIS Cortex-M3 Device Peripheral Access Layer Header File. This file contains all the peripheral register's definitions, bits definitions and memory mapping for STM32L1xx High-, Medium-density and Medium-density Plus devices. More...

Detailed Description

CMSIS Cortex-M3 Device Peripheral Access Layer Header File. This file contains all the peripheral register's definitions, bits definitions and memory mapping for STM32L1xx High-, Medium-density and Medium-density Plus devices.

Author
MCD Application Team
Version
V1.1.1
Date
09-March-2012 The file is the unique include file that the application programmer is using in the C source code, usually in main.c. This file contains:
  • Configuration section that allows to select:
    • The device used in the target application
    • To use or not the peripherals drivers in application code(i.e. code will be based on direct access to peripherals registers rather than drivers API), this option is controlled by "#define USE_STDPERIPH_DRIVER"
    • To change few application-specific parameters such as the HSE crystal frequency
  • Data structures and the address mapping for all peripherals
  • Peripheral's registers declarations and bits definition
  • Macros to access peripherals registers hardware
